@page "/concepts/organic"
@layout PgmStudio.Client.Layout.EditorLayout
@inject IJSRuntime JS
@inject HttpClient Http

@* Organic-generation demonstration page — the whole OrganicLane seeding pipeline on one page, each stage in
   its own panel with static explanatory text (the stages are fixed; only the geometry changes with the seed).
   The seed control re-runs the REAL generator (POST /api/sketch/generate/stages → OrganicLane.GrowStages) and
   re-renders every stage live via render/gen-stages.js. /concepts-style; see
   docs/contracts/organic-lane-generation.md. *@

<div class="editor-page">

<div id="topbar" class="topbar">
  <a href="/maps" class="topbar-breadcrumb-home" title="Back to dashboard">
    <i data-lucide="house"></i>
    <span>Studio</span>
  </a>
  <span class="topbar-sep">›</span>
  <span class="topbar-crumb">Organic Generation</span>
  <span class="topbar-crumb topbar-crumb--dim">pipeline</span>
  <div class="topbar-right">
    <span class="ds-file-list">OrganicLane.Grow · seed @seed</span>
    <ThemeToggle />
  </div>
</div>

<div id="ds-layout">
  <nav id="ds-nav" aria-label="Organic pipeline stages">
    <div class="ds-nav-group">Overview</div>
    <a href="#overview" @onclick:preventDefault="true" @onclick='() => Scroll("overview")'>Pipeline</a>
    <div class="ds-nav-group">Stages</div>
    <a href="#noise" @onclick:preventDefault="true" @onclick='() => Scroll("noise")'>1 · Noise field</a>
    <a href="#anchors" @onclick:preventDefault="true" @onclick='() => Scroll("anchors")'>2 · Anchor sampling</a>
    <a href="#spines" @onclick:preventDefault="true" @onclick='() => Scroll("spines")'>3 · Lane spines</a>
    <a href="#ribbons" @onclick:preventDefault="true" @onclick='() => Scroll("ribbons")'>4 · Ribbon hulls</a>
    <a href="#assembled" @onclick:preventDefault="true" @onclick='() => Scroll("assembled")'>5 · Assemble &amp; mirror</a>
    <div class="ds-nav-group">Reference</div>
    <a href="#legend" @onclick:preventDefault="true" @onclick='() => Scroll("legend")'>Legend &amp; knobs</a>
  </nav>

  <main id="ds-main">
    <header class="ds-intro" id="overview">
      <p class="ds-kicker">Lane generation · live</p>
      <h1>Organic seeding pipeline</h1>
      <p>
        The <code>Organic</code> archetype grows a team's island <strong>outward from a spawn hub</strong>
        into a few wool lanes, using a seeded noise field to place and bend them. This page lays out every
        stage of that growth as the <em>real</em> generator runs it — change the seed and every panel
        re-renders from a fresh <code>OrganicLane.GrowStages</code> run (no mock). Stages are fixed; only the
        geometry moves. The full design lives in <code>docs/contracts/organic-lane-generation.md</code>.
      </p>

      <div class="gen-controls">
        <div class="field gen-field">
          <label class="field-label">Seed</label>
          <NumberField Value="seed" ValueChanged="OnSeedChange" Min="1" />
        </div>
        <button class="action-btn action-btn--icon" @onclick="Reroll" title="Random seed" disabled="@loading">
          <i data-lucide="dices"></i>
        </button>
        <div class="field gen-field">
          <label class="field-label">Wools / team</label>
          <NumberField Value="wools" ValueChanged="OnWoolsChange" Min="1" Max="6" />
        </div>
        @if (loading) { <span class="gen-status">generating…</span> }
        else if (error is not null) { <span class="gen-status gen-status--error">@error</span> }
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="ds-section" id="noise">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div><p class="ds-kicker">Stage 1</p><h2>The value-noise field</h2></div>
        <p>A seeded <code>NoiseField</code> — a coherent [0,1] grid. Brighter = higher. Every later stage
          reads from it: where the wool tips spread, how the lanes bend, how the hull jitters.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gen-panel"><svg id="gen-stage-noise" class="gen-canvas"></svg></div>
    </section>

    <section class="ds-section" id="anchors">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div><p class="ds-kicker">Stage 2</p><h2>Anchor sampling</h2></div>
        <p>The hub sits above the mid line; short <strong>trunks</strong> reach toward it (future bridges).
          The <strong>wool tips</strong> are farthest-point sampled from the bright far band, each kept
          ≥ <code>MinHubAngle</code> from the others and the trunks so no thin slivers form.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gen-panel"><svg id="gen-stage-anchors" class="gen-canvas"></svg></div>
    </section>

    <section class="ds-section" id="spines">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div><p class="ds-kicker">Stage 3</p><h2>Lane spines</h2></div>
        <p>Each branch is a <strong>Catmull-Rom</strong> centerline: submerged hub nodes → noise-bent
          waypoints → tip. It is interpolating + centripetal, so the curve passes <em>through</em> the wool
          exactly and a short attach segment can't overshoot into a cusp.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gen-panel"><svg id="gen-stage-spines" class="gen-canvas"></svg></div>
    </section>

    <section class="ds-section" id="ribbons">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div><p class="ds-kicker">Stage 4</p><h2>Ribbon hulls</h2></div>
        <p><code>Lane.Ribbon</code> offsets each spine to a <strong>variable, jittered width</strong>
          (tapering toward the tip) → an organic hull, not a rectangle. Plus the hub <strong>plaza</strong>
          and any subtracted organic <strong>holes</strong>. This is the spine → area step.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gen-panel"><svg id="gen-stage-ribbons" class="gen-canvas"></svg></div>
    </section>

    <section class="ds-section" id="assembled">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div><p class="ds-kicker">Stage 5</p><h2>Assemble &amp; mirror</h2></div>
        <p>Union the hulls into one team island, then <code>mirror_z</code> it to the opponent across the mid
          line. Wools sit inset at the tips, the spawn on its spur; each trunk tip <strong>bridges</strong>
          the void to its mirror — two crossings, not one chokepoint.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gen-panel"><svg id="gen-stage-assembled" class="gen-canvas"></svg></div>
    </section>

    <section class="ds-section" id="legend">
      <div class="ds-section-heading">
        <div><p class="ds-kicker">Reference</p><h2>Legend &amp; knobs</h2></div>
        <p>Markers are consistent across the panels. The growth knobs (<code>LaneLayoutOptions</code>) are in
          the contract; seed + wools are exposed here.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="gen-legend">
        <span class="gen-legend-item"><span class="gen-swatch" style="background:var(--accent)"></span>noise value · wool objective</span>
        <span class="gen-legend-item"><span class="gen-swatch" style="background:var(--canvas-mirror-stroke)"></span>wool tip (anchor)</span>
        <span class="gen-legend-item"><span class="gen-swatch" style="background:var(--canvas-result-stroke)"></span>trunk / bridge anchor</span>
        <span class="gen-legend-item"><span class="gen-swatch" style="background:var(--color-error)"></span>spawn</span>
        <span class="gen-legend-item"><span class="gen-swatch" style="background:var(--text-muted)"></span>hub plaza</span>
        <span class="gen-legend-item"><span class="gen-swatch gen-swatch--mirror"></span>mirrored opponent island</span>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</div>

</div>
